import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='age_group', y='people', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people by age group?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age Group')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.legend(title='Age Groups', loc='upper right', labels=data['age_group'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='age_group', y='people', hue='sex', data=data, ci=None, estimator=sum)
    plt.title('How does the number of people vary by sex and age group?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Sex')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend in the number of people over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='People', loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
